1
00:00:00,416 --> 00:00:04,500
This door was for suspension [<i>shabeh</i>], and
their method of suspension had different types

2
00:00:05,125 --> 00:00:10,791
There was this one for the <i>balingo</i> [hoist], which
was located here, and another for light suspension

3
00:00:11,083 --> 00:00:14,208
They cuffed the hands behind the back with shackles

4
00:00:16,083 --> 00:00:19,375
They tied you up this way, and after a
while, they came back and lifted your hands

5
00:00:20,041 --> 00:00:26,166
Step by step, that’s how it went. He started at
first, and every so often, he lifted them higher

6
00:00:26,875 --> 00:00:30,125
Every hour or two, he came and lifted you a bit, to tighten it on you

7
00:00:30,208 --> 00:00:35,083
So your muscles would relax, then he
raised your hands as high as he could

8
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:39,208
You stayed like that for two, three, or four hours, sometimes even 10 hours

9
00:00:39,625 --> 00:00:43,791
Some prisoners stayed like that for days, and only
during prayer time would he release them to pray

10
00:00:44,041 --> 00:00:49,041
He let them go to the toilet, drink some water, then brought
them back. Of course, he left them thirsty for a while

11
00:00:50,041 --> 00:00:54,333
A man might remain hanging for two or three
days until he confessed to what they wanted

12
00:00:54,958 --> 00:01:01,958
You’d hear him saying, Write whatever you want
in the report, I’ll say exactly what you tell me

13
00:01:02,083 --> 00:01:04,791
He was even ready to record a video confession about it

14
00:01:05,250 --> 00:01:09,250
Just to save himself from that torment

15
00:01:12,875 --> 00:01:15,416
Here, of course, there was more than one door

16
00:01:15,875 --> 00:01:20,541
And this was the door where I was most often
suspended, because they used to hang me on it

17
00:01:21,458 --> 00:01:25,000
And directly behind it was the group cell where my father was

18
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:29,500
So he could hear my voice and the groans of
torture. They placed us this way on purpose

19
00:01:29,916 --> 00:01:32,500
And on the opposite side, they put
my brother in a nearby solitary cell

20
00:01:32,583 --> 00:01:34,750
So he would also hear the same sounds

21
00:01:35,375 --> 00:01:39,000
In that situation, I would often suppress

22
00:01:39,875 --> 00:01:42,583
The sounds of torture and my groaning, I held them in

23
00:01:42,666 --> 00:01:44,916
To spare my father’s feelings, so he wouldn’t hear that

24
00:01:45,833 --> 00:01:50,166
Because at the same time, he was making <i>duaa</i>
[supplication], silently, without letting out any sound

25
00:01:51,291 --> 00:01:56,083
He was crying, and I didn’t want to hear his voice either

26
00:01:56,208 --> 00:01:58,875
Because hearing his voice would make me break down even more

27
00:01:59,583 --> 00:02:05,041
The psychological torture was worse than the
physical one, especially for the prisoners

28
00:02:05,541 --> 00:02:13,166
I used to envy the prisoner who didn’t have a father
or brother detained with him in the same prison

29
00:02:13,833 --> 00:02:19,708
When you’re imprisoned alone, you
carry your sorrow and pain by yourself

30
00:02:19,875 --> 00:02:22,375
But in this case, we all carried each other’s grief

31
00:02:22,541 --> 00:02:27,083
Your worries, your father’s worries, and your
brother’s worries—all the same, all shared

32
00:02:27,583 --> 00:02:31,416
And also the worries of my brothers
outside. I had younger brothers

33
00:02:32,291 --> 00:02:38,041
Was my father grieving for us, or
for himself, or for his children outside?

34
00:02:38,750 --> 00:02:46,416
That was what affected me and my father most deeply

35
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:49,083
That they tortured me right in this area

36
00:02:49,666 --> 00:02:52,916
Or in the investigation room. They
opened the door, it was right nearby

37
00:02:53,375 --> 00:02:56,500
They opened the investigation room door
and this door, so the sound would carry

38
00:02:57,458 --> 00:03:00,750
The sound of torture reached the prisoners
more clearly, for psychological effect

39
00:03:03,208 --> 00:03:08,166
And there were many doors. Sometimes
there were more than two or three

40
00:03:08,333 --> 00:03:10,791
Or even four people suspended at the same time

41
00:03:11,583 --> 00:03:15,083
Sometimes I was suspended here, and this door opened and closed

42
00:03:15,625 --> 00:03:18,041
Sometimes they hung people from it for two or three hours

43
00:03:18,666 --> 00:03:24,291
You’d see people go numb—you could only hear faint groaning

44
00:03:24,666 --> 00:03:29,375
Once, I was suspended beside
another man, hung right next to him

45
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:31,750
He had been hanging for a day or two

46
00:03:32,375 --> 00:03:38,041
Two hours passed, maybe more, before I even
realized someone was suspended beside me

47
00:03:38,416 --> 00:03:41,000
The interrogator came and spoke to
him, and I started answering instead

48
00:03:41,083 --> 00:03:46,625
He said to me, I’m not talking to you, and then I
heard the voice of the prisoner hanging next to me

49
00:03:46,708 --> 00:03:50,583
I hadn’t even realized he was there, because
he had been tortured so much that he couldn’t speak
